        <h1>Control</h1>
            <h3>What learnings did you take from the chapter</h3>
              <p>
                That letting go of your anoyances and frustrations is very important. Its something i am very good at in some aspects in my life and completly unable to do with other aspects, I'll be using the teachings in this chapter to try to get more balance in the difficult areas, I liked they way he talked about concentrating on holding your bad feelings in your hand and then letting them go.
              </p>
            <h3>How did you find the two minutes of mindfulness</h3>
              <p>
                Some times I find it really easy to do up to 10 minutes and sometimes I just cant stay focused for more than a minute. i have started using the body scan to try to get to sleep. 
              </p>
            <h3>When you were pair programming, did you exercise any of your emotional intelligence skills?</h3>
              <p> 
                I honestly didnt need to, we worked really well together. Im sure there will be a time when i need to but this time was realy enjoyable. 
